children.subject: I would suggest folks without a python 2.7.x install to install anaconda2, activate navigator, and code in spyder.

history.content:
In case this helps someone else...

If you are on a Mac, these were the three commands I ran to get NumPy installed on my computer (and have the template code working):

sudo pip install --user --upgrade pip
sudo pip install --user -U pip setuptools
sudo pip install --user -U pip numpy

This is for a Mac, and your mileage may vary (at work I have a Mac as well, but my Python installation has been so customized over the years than the above commands don't work). If you don't have too many custom stuff, the above should get you up and running.

After this, go to the folder with the Bloom Filter code (the one you downloaded and unzip it), and run the following:

python bloom.py -c testConfigHashType2.txt -i testInput.txt -o testOutput.txt -v validResHashType2.txt 

The output should be the following:
